## 6. JudgeGuard Log Analysis

Your Kaggle kernel (Tesla P100, 17.1 GB VRAM, PyTorch 2.8+CUDA) ran JudgeGuard v2.0 with:
- **Model used:** `distilgpt2` (fallback, Gemma-2B not found in `/kaggle/input`)
- **Accuracy:** 3/4 scenarios (75%) — Feature Engineering was incorrectly BLOCKED by distilgpt2 VetoBoard
- **Known bug:** `distilgpt2` is too small for nuanced code safety decisions. Real deployment needs Gemma-2B or larger.
- **Latency:** avg 1.51s/call — acceptable for guard usage
- **JudgeGuardLite:** Detected 3 errors in demo CSV (missing [id](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/playground-s6e2-heart-disease/s6e2_utils.py#169-203), `target`, 1 NaN)

> [!NOTE]
> The VetoBoard false-positive on Feature Engineering is a known issue with small LLMs. The `distilgpt2` VetoBoard needs a stronger model (Gemma-7B+) or rule-based fallback for code-safety decisions.

